{"type":"message","id":"f03b2a11","parentId":"f32e2fcc","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:16:17.942Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_aufsrh6vkswt_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[mutation applied] APPENDED to research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\r\n[LLM] response length: 5494\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='' file='' new_len=0\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation parse failed] old='' file='the' new_len=0\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 031543 - The TIC experiment requires implementing a classifier on existing pulse logs to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis. The experiment design is documented but the implementation is pending.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"glow-forest","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[mutation applied] APPENDED to research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\r\n[LLM] response length: 5494\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='' file='' new_len=0\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation parse failed] old='' file='the' new_len=0\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 031543 - The TIC experiment requires implementing a classifier on existing pulse logs to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis. The experiment design is documented but the implementation is pending.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774336577940}}
{"type":"message","id":"0d67de59","parentId":"f03b2a11","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:16:17.944Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_aufsrh6vkswt_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 031446\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: experiments/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nFrom the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- Pending tasks include: Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI, Define `significance` scoring, Tune λ empirically, Wire Breakaway to TemporalAttention backend, Measure compression ratio\r\n- Current focus: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight suggests these are the SAME problem\r\n- NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment - Implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe most impactful immediate action is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment. This tests the core hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\nLet me implement the TIC classifier on the existing pulse logs.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight identifies that discovering invariants (causal structure) is the same problem as compression. The TIC experiment is the logical next step to validate this hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier experiment script that analyzes pulse logs to identify invariant vs variant patterns, and measures prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n# Phase: Phase 1 Advancement - COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n# Created: 2026-03-24\r\n# Goal: Validate that causal structure = invariant structure\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nAn LLM that can identify temporal invariants across pulse logs has discovered causal relationships.\r\nCompression that preserves invariants IS causal discovery.\r\n\r\n## Method\r\n1. Extract features from last 20 pulse logs\r\n2. Classify each feature as INVARIANT (stable across sessions) or VARIANT (changing)\r\n3. Use invariants to predict next pulse content\r\n4. Measure accuracy against success criteria\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n# See: experiments/tic_classifier.py\r\n\r\n## Pulse Log Files (n=20)\r\n- logs/pulse_2026-03-*.md\r\n\r\n## Results (to be filled)\r\n- classification_accuracy: pending\r\n- prediction_accuracy: pending\r\n- invariants_found: []\r\n- variants_found: []\r\n\r\n## Next Steps\r\n1. Run TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n2. Validate against success criteria\r\n3. If pass: Phase 1 and Phase 2 collapse into unified TIC problem\r\n4. If fail: Refine λ parameter and retry\r\nfile: research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Classifier\r\n================================================\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\nInput: Last 20 pulse logs\r\nOutput: Invariant/variant classification + next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\nSuccess: >70% classification, >60% prediction\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple\r\n\r\nPULSE_LOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nMIN_LOGS = 5  # Minimum logs needed for meaningful analysis\r\n\r\ndef extract_features(pulse_file: Path) -> Dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract structural features from a pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    content = pulse_file.read_text()\r\n    \r\n    features = {\r\n        'filename': pulse_file.name,\r\n        'has_observation': '### OBSERVATION' in content,\r\n        'has_action': '### ACTION' in content,\r\n        'has_mutation': '### MUTATION' in content,\r\n        'num_headers': len(re.findall(r'^### ', content, re.MULTILINE)),\r\n        'num_code_blocks': len(re.findall(r'```', content)),\r\n        'num_bullets': len(re.findall(r'^\\s*[-*+]\\s', content, re.MULTILINE)),\r\n        'num_checkboxes': len(re.findall(r'\\[[ x]\\]\\s', content)),\r\n        'has_goal_ref': 'goal' in content.lower(),\r\n        'has_phase_ref': 'phase' in content.lower(),\r\n        'has_pending_ref': 'pending' in content.lower(),\r\n        'content_length': len(content),\r\n        'has_mutation_applied': 'No mutations applied' not in content,\r\n    }\r\n    return features\r\n\r\ndef load_pulse_logs(n: int = 20) -> List[Dict]:\r\n    \"\"\"Load the n most recent pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    logs = sorted(PULSE_LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), reverse=True)[:n]\r\n    \r\n    if len(logs) < MIN_LOGS:\r\n        print(f\"Warning: Only {len(logs)} logs found (need {MIN_LOGS})\")\r\n    \r\n    return [extract_features(log) for log in logs]\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant(feature_values: List, threshold: float = 0.8) -> bool:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Classify a feature as INVARIANT if its value is stable across sessions.\r\n    INVARIANT = appears in >= threshold fraction of logs\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    if not feature_values:\r\n        return False\r\n    \r\n    # For boolean features\r\n    if all(isinstance(v, bool) for v in feature_values):\r\n        true_count = sum(1 for v in feature_values if v)\r\n        return true_count / len(feature_values) >= threshold\r\n    \r\n    # For numeric features - check variance\r\n    if all(isinstance(v, (int, float)) for v in feature_values):\r\n        if len(set(feature_values)) == 1:\r\n            return True  # Perfect invariance\r\n        # Coefficient of variation\r\n        mean = sum(feature_values) / len(feature_values)\r\n        if mean == 0:\r\n            return True\r\n        variance = sum((v - mean) ** 2 for v in feature_values) /\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:15:23\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774336577942}}
