{"type":"message","id":"aac02766","parentId":"f03b1b67","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:16:43.170Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ujarw2chzm6q_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 031543\n\n## Applied Mutations\nJust applied: research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md (appended)\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n- Pending items include implementing TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n- Next action is to implement TIC classifier\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step would be to actually implement the Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) classifier on the pulse log files. This would involve:\r\n1. Reading the pulse logs\r\n2. Implementing the invariant/variant classification\r\n3. Testing prediction of next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me first check what pulse logs exist and look at the TIC experiment doc to understand what needs to be implemented.\r\n\r\nActually, I should look at the existing files to understand the current state better before making changes. But since I'm stateless and this is a fresh pulse, I need to be careful about what I do.\r\n\r\nGiven the context, the most actionable thing would be to:\r\n1. Create the TIC classifier implementation\r\n2. Or update the state/goals to reflect progress\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist and create the TIC classifier. I'll need to create a Python script or similar that implements the TIC logic.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending items:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nThis is the clear next action. I should create a script that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse log files\r\n2. Extracts content/features from them\r\n3. Classifies invariant vs variant elements\r\n4. Attempts to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script for this.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires implementing a classifier on existing pulse logs to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis. The experiment design is documented but the implementation is pending.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier script that will analyze pulse logs for invariants and test next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC: Temporal Invariance Compression Classifier\r\nTests the hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nPULSE_LOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nTIC_RESULTS_FILE = Path(\"state/tic_results.json\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_pulse_content(pulse_file):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract key content from a pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    content = pulse_file.read_text()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract structured sections\r\n    observations = re.findall(r'### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?=\\n###|\\Z)', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    actions = re.findall(r'### ACTION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?=\\n###|\\Z)', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    mutations = re.findall(r'### MUTATION\\s*\\n```\\s*\\n(.*?)```', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        'observations': [o.strip() for o in observations],\r\n        'actions': [a.strip() for a in actions],\r\n        'mutations': [m.strip() for m in mutations],\r\n        'raw': content\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef extract_invariants(pulse_data_list):\r\n    \"\"\"Find elements that persist across pulses (invariants).\"\"\"\r\n    # Extract all tokens/patterns\r\n    all_observations = [o for p in pulse_data_list for o in p['observations']]\r\n    all_actions = [a for p in pulse_data_list for a in p['actions']]\r\n    \r\n    # Count frequencies\r\n    obs_counter = Counter(all_observations)\r\n    act_counter = Counter(all_actions)\r\n    \r\n    # Invariants = elements appearing >= 2 times (threshold configurable)\r\n    invariance_threshold = 2\r\n    invariants = {\r\n        'observations': {k: v for k, v in obs_counter.items() if v >= invariance_threshold},\r\n        'actions': {k: v for k, v in act_counter.items() if v >= invariance_threshold},\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return invariants\r\n\r\ndef calculate_invariant_ratio(pulse_data_list, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Calculate ratio of invariant content per pulse.\"\"\"\r\n    results = []\r\n    for i, pulse in enumerate(pulse_data_list):\r\n        total_obs = len(pulse['observations'])\r\n        total_act = len(pulse['actions'])\r\n        \r\n        inv_obs = sum(1 for o in pulse['observations'] if o in invariants['observations'])\r\n        inv_act = sum(1 for a in pulse['actions'] if a in invariants['actions'])\r\n        \r\n        ratio = (inv_obs + inv_act) / max(1, total_obs + total_act)\r\n        results.append(ratio)\r\n    \r\n    return results\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(pulse_data_list, invariants, lookback=3):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next pulse content based on invariant patterns.\"\"\"\r\n    predictions = []\r\n    actuals = []\r\n    \r\n    for i in range(lookback, len(pulse_data_list)):\r\n        # Predict using previous `lookback` pulses\r\n        context = pulse_data_list[i-lookback:i]\r\n        next_pulse = pulse_data_list[i]\r\n        \r\n        # Simple prediction: most common invariant in context\r\n        predicted_obs = set()\r\n        predicted_act = set()\r\n        \r\n        for p in context:\r\n            for o in p['observations']:\r\n                if o in invariants['observations']:\r\n                    predicted_obs.add(o)\r\n            for a in p['actions']:\r\n                if a in invariants['actions']:\r\n                    predicted_act.add(a)\r\n        \r\n        # Calculate overlap with actual\r\n        actual_obs = set(next_pulse['observations'])\r\n        actual_act = set(next_pulse['actions'])\r\n        \r\n        obs_overlap = len(predicted_obs & actual_obs) / max(1, len(actual_obs))\r\n        act_overlap = len(predicted_act & actual_act) / max(1, len(actual_act))\r\n        \r\n        predictions.append((obs_overlap\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:16:17\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774336603168}}
